# ---
# Line endings: CRLF/LF handling
#
# To ensure consistent line endings across Windows (CRLF) and Linux/macOS (LF),
# use a .gitattributes file in your repository root with the following content:
#
#   * text=auto
#
# This will make Git handle line endings automatically for all text files.
#
# You do NOT need to ignore files based on line endings in .gitignore.
#
# If you have files that must always use LF or CRLF, specify them in .gitattributes.
#
# Example .gitattributes:
#   *.sh text eol=lf
#   *.bat text eol=crlf
#
# See: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitattributes#_end_of_line_conversion
